  { q: "Who owns Middleby Marshall?", a: "Middleby Marshall has been part of Middleby Corporation since 1998 when Middleby acquired the brand. Middleby Marshall is headquartered in Elgin, Illinois, and has manufactured commercial conveyor pizza ovens since 1888 — making it one of the oldest continuously-operating conveyor-oven specialists in the United States. Important disambiguation: Middleby Marshall (pizza conveyor ovens) is distinct from Middleby Viking/Marvel (residential refrigeration), and Middleby Corporation (the parent — 30+ brands across cooking and refrigeration divisions) is the umbrella company, not the pizza-oven specific brand. The Middleby family includes Blodgett ovens, TurboChef rapid-cook, Southbend ranges, Lang clamshell grills, Bakers Pride pizza deck ovens, Star Manufacturing, Jade Range, Viking Commercial, Anets fryers, and roughly a dozen other cooking brands — all sharing Middleby's parts chain and service infrastructure." },
  { q: "What's the difference between Middleby Marshall PS series and WOW oven?", a: "Two generations of the same conveyor pizza oven line. PS series is the long-running chain-pizza workhorse — PS200, PS220, PS350, PS360, PS536, PS540, PS555, PS570 configurations across different sizes and throughput capacities. The PS line has been the OEM standard for major chain pizza franchises for decades; parts availability is strong, service procedures well-documented. WOW oven is the current-generation high-volume conveyor with bi-directional air-flow technology — engineered for highest-throughput chain operations where PS-series spec would constrain peak-hour pizza production. Marshall 9100 is a legacy model still in service at older franchise locations; parts for Marshall 9100 are increasingly scarce (honest repair-vs-replace framing required on 15-plus-year units). CTX is another legacy conveyor line being phased out." },
  { q: "Which LA pizza chain franchises run Middleby Marshall?", a: "Nearly all of them. Middleby Marshall is the OEM pizza conveyor oven standard across the major chain pizza franchises operating in LA County: Domino's Pizza (100+ LA locations), Pizza Hut, Papa John's Pizza, Little Caesars, Marco's Pizza, and comparable chain operations. The OEM relationship means every franchise buildout includes Middleby Marshall conveyor ovens per corporate spec; franchise operators can't substitute competing brands without corporate approval. For LA service, this creates substantial franchise-segment dispatch volume — chain pizza oven failures during delivery-peak hours (evenings, weekends) are revenue-critical events requiring emergency response." },
  { q: "What breaks most on Middleby Marshall conveyor ovens?", a: "Top service calls we run in LA on Middleby Marshall equipment: conveyor belt tension (wears from continuous operation, gradually slackens causing cook-time inconsistency); burner ignitor assembly (high-cycle firing at 500+ ignitions per day wears electrodes); thermostat drift over 3–5 year service windows (cook temperatures drift off spec, pizza quality affected); WOW oven air-flow sensor malfunctions (bi-directional air-flow calibration requires the sensor to function correctly; drift causes cook-consistency problems); high-limit reset failures (safety thermostat trips under certain failure modes, pizza line stops). Belt replacement is the most common emergency call; typical belt-replacement service 60–120 minutes depending on belt condition and accessibility." },
  { q: "Can you handle a chain franchise service call from a PS-series failure during dinner rush?", a: "Yes — this is a substantial part of our LA commercial pizza oven service work. Chain franchise operations have specific service-coordination requirements: franchise operators coordinate through corporate maintenance programs, authorized Middleby Marshall service providers, and franchise-specific documentation. Our role is typically emergency response during service windows when corporate-authorized dispatch timing doesn't fit the franchise operator's revenue-critical cadence, out-of-warranty coverage on older PS units, and consolidated service for LA-based franchise groups running multiple locations. Documentation appropriate for franchise maintenance records provided alongside standard work orders. Call (424) 325-0520 and specify \"Middleby Marshall pizza oven emergency\" — dispatch routes accordingly." },
  { q: "Middleby family cross-brand service — what can you cover?", a: "Middleby Corporation's commercial foodservice portfolio spans Middleby Marshall (pizza conveyor — this page), Blodgett (pizza deck + convection), TurboChef (rapid-cook), Southbend (ranges + ovens), Lang (clamshell grills + Mini-Rack banquet roasters), Bakers Pride (pizza deck + convection), Star Manufacturing, Jade Range, Viking Commercial (restaurant line), Anets (fryers), Holman, and roughly a dozen more cooking-side brands. For LA kitchens running multi-Middleby configurations — common at chain franchise operations and at mid-upper restaurant kitchens where Middleby equipment packages came through single-dealer build-outs — a single service call can address failures across multiple Middleby brands in the same visit. Shared Middleby parts infrastructure; single service account." },
  { q: "What does Middleby Marshall pizza oven repair cost in LA?", a: "$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Typical Middleby Marshall service ranges: thermostat $200–$340, burner ignitor $240–$400, high-limit reset service $180–$320, door gasket / end panel $220–$380, gas valve $280–$480, conveyor belt tension adjustment $180–$320, conveyor belt replacement $380–$640, air-flow sensor (WOW) $300–$500, pilot / spark electrode $220–$380, control board / Tempset module $750–$1,400, PS-series burner refurbish $500–$820. Most Middleby Marshall calls land $380–$800 parts-and-labor. WOW-specific and belt-replacement jobs run at the higher end. See our <a href=\"/price-list/commercial-oven-repair-cost/\">commercial oven repair cost guide</a>." }
];

