  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Middleby Marshall — the chain pizza OEM, Elgin IL since 1888</h2>
    <p>Middleby Marshall has manufactured commercial conveyor pizza ovens from Elgin, Illinois since 1888 — making it one of the oldest continuously-operating conveyor-oven specialists in the United States. Middleby Corporation acquired Middleby Marshall in 1998 and integrated it into Middleby's commercial foodservice portfolio alongside Blodgett ovens (1997), Southbend ranges (2010), TurboChef rapid-cook (2013), Lang clamshell grills (2018), Bakers Pride pizza deck ovens (1999), and roughly a dozen other cooking brands.</p>
    <p>Important disambiguation: Middleby Marshall is the pizza conveyor oven specialist brand. Middleby Corporation (the parent company) is a large commercial foodservice conglomerate with 30+ brands spanning both cooking and refrigeration divisions. Middleby Viking and Middleby Marvel are the residential refrigeration brands within the Middleby Corp portfolio — those are different companies from Middleby Marshall despite the shared "Middleby" name. When sourcing parts or scheduling service for pizza conveyor ovens, specify "Middleby Marshall" (or the specific PS/WOW/CTX/Marshall 9100 model) to route correctly.</p>
    <p>The chain-pizza OEM relationship is Middleby Marshall's defining industry position. For decades, Middleby Marshall conveyor pizza ovens have been spec'd as OEM standard across the major US chain pizza franchises: Domino's (100-plus LA County locations, nationwide standard), Pizza Hut, Papa John's, Little Caesars, Marco's Pizza, and comparable chains. Every franchise buildout includes Middleby Marshall ovens per corporate specification; franchise operators can't substitute competing brands without corporate approval. This creates substantial chain-segment service volume for LA operators — franchise pizza oven failures during delivery-peak hours are revenue-critical events.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Middleby Marshall pizza ovens we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>PS Series — flagship conveyor</h3><p>The chain-pizza conveyor oven workhorse. PS200 / PS220 smaller throughput; PS350 / PS360 mid-range (most common franchise installation); PS536 / PS540 / PS555 / PS570 higher throughput for high-volume operations. Long track record in LA franchise service. Service: thermostat, burner ignitor, conveyor belt tension + replacement, gas valve, high-limit reset.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>WOW Oven — high-volume current-gen</h3><p>Current-generation high-volume conveyor with bi-directional air-flow technology — engineered for highest-throughput chain operations where PS-series spec would constrain peak-hour pizza production. Service includes specialized air-flow sensor calibration as a distinct diagnostic domain beyond standard PS-series service.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>CTX — legacy conveyor</h3><p>Legacy CTX conveyor line being phased out across Middleby Marshall's lineup. Still in service at older franchise locations and independent pizza operations that installed CTX during its production run. Parts availability moderate; honest repair-vs-replace guidance on 10-plus-year CTX units.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Marshall 9100 — legacy</h3><p>Older legacy Marshall conveyor model. Still in service at long-tenure LA pizza operations, older franchise locations. Parts availability increasingly constrained — some components require substitution or cross-reference. Honest repair-vs-replace framing on 15-plus-year Marshall 9100 units; sometimes replacement is the sensible call.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>LA chain pizza franchise cluster — Middleby Marshall at 200+ locations</h2>
    <p>LA County hosts one of the densest chain pizza franchise concentrations in the United States. Specific franchise systems running Middleby Marshall OEM:</p>
    <ul class="check-list">
      <li><b>Domino's Pizza</b> — 100+ LA County franchise locations. Middleby Marshall PS series is the Domino's corporate standard; PS350/360 are the most common installations. WOW ovens appear at newer high-volume locations.</li>
      <li><b>Pizza Hut</b> — Significant LA franchise presence including delivery-only, counter-service, and full-service formats. Middleby Marshall PS series standard.</li>
      <li><b>Papa John's Pizza</b> — LA franchise cluster with Middleby Marshall conveyor standard.</li>
      <li><b>Little Caesars</b> — Hot-N-Ready model depends on continuous conveyor production; Middleby Marshall conveyors throughout LA franchise system.</li>
      <li><b>Marco's Pizza</b> — Growing LA presence; Middleby Marshall spec.</li>
      <li><b>Blaze Pizza, MOD Pizza, Pieology</b> — Fast-casual format pizza chains, some running Middleby Marshall though some spec alternate conveyor brands.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Franchise service coordinates through franchise operators and corporate maintenance programs. Our role in the chain-franchise segment is typically emergency response during service windows, out-of-warranty coverage on older PS units, consolidated service for LA-based franchise groups running multiple locations, and documentation for franchise maintenance records. Beyond chain franchises, Middleby Marshall appears at independent pizza operations that specified conveyor technology during buildout — less common than deck ovens at the independent-artisan end of the market but present.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Conveyor belt, air-flow, and common Middleby Marshall service patterns</h2>
    <ul class="check-list">
      <li><b>Conveyor belt tension</b> — belts wear from continuous operation at 300+ cycles per service day. Tension gradually slackens; pizza cook-time drifts from spec. Tension-adjustment service 30–60 minutes; full belt replacement 60–120 minutes depending on model and accessibility.</li>
      <li><b>Burner ignitor assembly</b> — high-cycle firing at 500+ ignitions per day wears electrode surfaces. Delayed ignition or complete ignition failure symptoms. 45-minute service typically.</li>
      <li><b>Thermostat drift</b> — drifts over 3–5 year service windows. Cook temperatures drift off spec; pizza quality and consistency affected. Replacement or recalibration 30–60 minutes.</li>
      <li><b>WOW oven air-flow sensor</b> — bi-directional air-flow calibration depends on the sensor functioning correctly. Drift causes cook-consistency problems (burned top, under-baked bottom, or vice versa). Specialized diagnostic domain; most competitor LA appliance techs can't diagnose WOW air-flow issues.</li>
      <li><b>High-limit reset failures</b> — safety thermostat trips under certain failure modes; pizza line stops. Reset service plus root-cause investigation 45–90 minutes.</li>
      <li><b>Tempset module / control board</b> — electronic control failures on newer Middleby Marshall models. Parts from Middleby Chicago/Elgin parts chain, 2–5 day lead time typical.</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

